body:
Flutter projects are not Gradle-based Android projects so a number of features provided by Android Studio are not available to Flutter programmers.

- [x] When opening / editing plugin files in the android/ or ios/ directories, have an easy way for the user to open the correct external editor.
- [x] Code completion in the Java or Kotlin code of an Android module should be supported.
- [x] The Project list view should default to `Project` not `Android`.
     [I think this was fixed by Android Studio at the beginning of May]
- [x] The Project list view setting should be preserved.
     [I think this was fixed by Android Studio at the beginning of May]
- [x] The AVD Manager should always be available.
- [x] The framework detector should not report that an Android framework has been detected.
- [ ] Support indexing of C++ files to allow navigation, completion, etc.
- [x] Support off-line project creation #2099
